- 'fertile ground' refers to job postings that the user is qualified for;
- 'expansive world' represents the industry of the job;
- 'where' refers to the location of the job posting;
- 'seasoned explorer' is the user with the username 'admin';
- 'vast journey' represents the user's experience;
- 'knowledge' signifies the user's education level;
- 'tools' symbolize the skills required for the job;
- The condition 'user_experience >= experience_required' ensures the user's journey is worthy enough for the job ground;
- 'tool' must be present, i.e., 'skill_id IS NOT NULL', indicating the job requires a specific skill for cultivation.

